article_title: City Ice Groomer is Lord of the Rink
article_text:
They call him the Zeus of the ice.

Nelson Corporan rises at 4:30 a.m. five days a week and takes the D train from Washington Heights to 50th street to spend the predawn hours buffing the ice rink in Rockefeller Center to gleaming perfection.

article_summary:
Nelson Corporan rises at 4:30 a.m. five days a week and takes the D train from Washington Heights to 50th street to spend the predawn hours buffing the ice rink in Rockefeller Center to gleaming perfection.
They call him the Zeus of the ice.
